<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
If String1 is NULL while String1Max > 0 then FormatLen1 is set to String1Max and the code reaches memchr(String1, '\n', FormatLen1). This results in memchr(NULL, '\n', n) (a null-pointer access), which violates Rule 21.17. Another possible violation is if String1Max does not actually reflect the underlying object size (caller-provided size too large) so FormatLen1 > actual object length — the memchr call would then read beyond the object bounds.
</scenario>

